Citation.sTitle: Determination and Correlation of Solubilities of Lauric Acid in Eight Alcohols
Citation.sAbstract: The solubilities of lauric acid in methanol, ethanol, propanol, n-butanol, n-pentanol, n-hexanol, isobutanol, and isoamylol were measured by synthetic method in the temperature ranging from (276.17 to 306.12) K. Results of these measurements were correlated by the modified Apelblat equation, the ?h equation and activity coefficient models (NRTL and UNIQUAC). It was found that the modified Apelblat equation and the ?h equation gave better correlation results. The thermodynamic properties of the solution process, including the Gibbs energy, enthalpy, and entropy were calculated by the van t Hoff analysis.
